		</group>
	</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1>
	<title>Description</title>
	<para>
		&p; finds entries in the &d; which matches a pattern (regular
		expression). Moreover, it can run an interactive version of the
		dictionary interface.
	</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
	<title>Options</title>
	<para>
		&p; accepts the following options:
	</para>

	<variablelist>
		<varlistentry>
			<term><option>-e</option></term>
			<term><option>--entry-only</option></term>
			<listitem>
				<para>Display only entries, not their definitions.</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term><option>-d</option></term>
			<term><option>--deep</option></term>
			<listitem>
				<para>Search through definitions, not only entries.</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term><option><replaceable>pattern</replaceable></option></term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
					A pattern which an entry (or definition, if
					<option>--deep</option> were chosen) should match to be
					displayed.
				</para>
				<para>
					The pattern is treated as case-insensitive POSIX Extended
					Regular Expression.
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term><option>-i</option></term>
			<term><option>--ui</option></term>
			<listitem>
				<para>Run an interactive version of the dictionary interface.</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term><option>-h</option></term>
			<term><option>--help</option></term>
			<listitem>
				<para>Display help and exit.</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
			<term><option>-v</option></term>
			<term><option>--version</option></term>
			<listitem>
          		<para>Output version information and exit.</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>
	</variablelist>
</refsect1>

